WEBVTT

00:00:06.340 --> 00:00:07.730
She's fully recovered.

00:00:10.240 --> 00:00:13.990
{\an8}El Condor Pasa

00:00:10.320 --> 00:00:13.990
<i>The world was right in front of my eyes…</i>

00:00:13.990 --> 00:00:17.280
<i>I need to run even faster.</i>

00:00:37.090 --> 00:00:38.970
I need to do more!

00:00:44.810 --> 00:00:45.690
Go!

00:00:45.690 --> 00:00:48.310
You can do it!

00:00:48.310 --> 00:00:50.960
She's got real drive.

00:00:50.960 --> 00:00:53.140
I need to do more, too.

00:00:53.140 --> 00:00:55.560
Suzuka, we should run, too.

00:00:55.560 --> 00:00:56.410
Yeah!

00:00:57.700 --> 00:00:59.580
If you want that Dream Trophy,

00:00:59.580 --> 00:01:01.660
then the whole team has to win.

00:01:01.660 --> 00:01:05.810
We've practiced and have the will.

00:01:05.810 --> 00:01:07.530
Don't lose to Rigil!

00:01:07.530 --> 00:01:08.580
Right!

00:01:08.580 --> 00:01:11.670
All right. Spe, you have the Kyoto Daishoten,

00:01:11.670 --> 00:01:13.120
which is a bellwether for the fall races.

00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:16.260
Show everyone what Spica's made of out there!

00:01:16.260 --> 00:01:16.800
Right!

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:19.690
Team Spica, let's do this!

00:01:19.690 --> 00:01:21.810
Yeah!

00:01:20.060 --> 00:01:21.810
You're in the way!

00:01:22.420 --> 00:01:24.310
<i>It's one of Team Spica's members to watch!</i>

00:01:24.310 --> 00:01:26.730
<i>Special Week is entering the course.</i>

00:01:28.950 --> 00:01:32.820
Special Week's body seems much sturdier now.

00:01:32.820 --> 00:01:36.900
<i>We have the Fall Tennoushou coming up,
so it'll be interesting to see what happens.</i>

00:01:37.320 --> 00:01:42.520
<i>Special Week is at her peak.
If I keep an eye on her, I'll win.</i>

00:01:42.520 --> 00:01:43.900
<i>I can do this!</i>

00:01:43.900 --> 00:01:46.840
Special Week seems bigger.

00:01:46.840 --> 00:01:48.670
She's got a different aura to her!

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:50.710
<i>I'm not going to hesitate any longer.</i>

00:01:51.160 --> 00:01:54.920
<i>I'm going to show them how hard I've trained!</i>

00:01:55.460 --> 00:01:57.690
<i>Special Week has come in 7th!</i>

00:01:57.690 --> 00:01:58.630
<i>A complete defeat!</i>

00:01:58.630 --> 00:02:00.610
<i>T.M. Opera O has come in 3rd!</i>

00:02:01.640 --> 00:02:03.860
I picked the wrong person to follow!

00:02:06.600 --> 00:02:08.980
Why?!

00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:19.920
Do you hear the fanfare as
we race towards the finish?

00:02:19.920 --> 00:02:26.450
I want to see that shining future with you

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:34.800
{\an8}Umamusume

00:02:30.370 --> 00:02:34.670
{\an8}Pretty Derby

00:02:36.680 --> 00:02:42.400
If we just start to run, that's
where our story will begin

00:02:42.400 --> 00:02:47.420
It's always waiting right in front of us

00:02:47.420 --> 00:02:53.030
If you reach out just a little
more, we can seize that glory

00:02:53.030 --> 00:02:59.890
Aim for the top, challenge
them all, and it's off to the races

00:03:00.700 --> 00:03:05.890
Even the goddess of victory will be dazzled

00:03:05.890 --> 00:03:13.170
By your big debut that's just around the bend

00:03:13.170 --> 00:03:18.590
So can you hear the fanfare
as we race towards the finish?

00:03:18.590 --> 00:03:24.060
I want to see that shining future with you

00:03:24.060 --> 00:03:29.570
Let's overtake them all! It's
a track laid out just for you!

00:03:29.570 --> 00:03:37.330
Your dreams are at the finish if you believe

00:03:39.030 --> 00:03:43.030
{\an8}Race 10

00:03:39.030 --> 00:03:43.030
{\an8}No Matter How Many Times I Lose

00:03:43.370 --> 00:03:45.490
El, welcome back.

00:03:45.490 --> 00:03:48.330
You were so close during that race.

00:03:48.330 --> 00:03:51.790
It was close, but second is still second.

00:03:51.790 --> 00:03:55.210
I'm going to start training right away
so that I can get first next time!

00:04:03.260 --> 00:04:05.970
Spe-chan!

00:04:05.970 --> 00:04:07.250
El-chan!

00:04:07.250 --> 00:04:09.830
I just got back!

00:04:09.830 --> 00:04:11.310
Welcome back.

00:04:11.310 --> 00:04:14.790
I saw the Kyoto Daishoten on TV.

00:04:14.790 --> 00:04:16.760
Don't get depressed about coming in 7th.

00:04:17.440 --> 00:04:19.680
Everyone has off days.

00:04:20.650 --> 00:04:22.650
Sometimes, nothing goes the way you want.

00:04:23.330 --> 00:04:25.470
Hmm? You seem bigger than before.

00:04:25.470 --> 00:04:29.120
El, stop kicking Spe-chan
while she's down.

00:04:29.120 --> 00:04:31.040
Sorry about that.

00:04:31.040 --> 00:04:32.570
Anyway, let's go.

00:04:31.810 --> 00:04:36.540
{\an8}Yep, I'm definitely back in Japan!

00:04:36.540 --> 00:04:40.130
Spe, it doesn't help to think about
things that have already happened.

00:04:40.500 --> 00:04:42.240
The Fall Tennoushou is next.

00:04:42.240 --> 00:04:44.970
I have the Japan Cup in my sights after that.

00:04:44.970 --> 00:04:48.440
The Fall Tennoushou…

00:04:48.440 --> 00:04:51.930
<i>That's right. It's the race
Suzuka got hurt in last year.</i>

00:04:52.660 --> 00:04:54.520
<i>I can't lose that.</i>

00:04:54.520 --> 00:04:57.030
Trainer, what are we doing today?

00:04:57.030 --> 00:04:59.080
Bring whatever you've got!

00:05:02.120 --> 00:05:04.590
You guys are getting way too worked up.

00:05:04.590 --> 00:05:06.660
Don't wear yourselves out.

00:05:06.660 --> 00:05:07.610
Especially you, Spe!

00:05:07.610 --> 00:05:08.790
R-Right.

00:05:08.790 --> 00:05:11.450
Your last race didn't end well because
you didn't cool down properly.

00:05:11.800 --> 00:05:14.000
Were you training in secret?

00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:15.620
Uh? Well…

00:05:16.970 --> 00:05:17.970
I've decided!

00:05:17.970 --> 00:05:20.260
You guys are getting some rest!

00:05:20.260 --> 00:05:22.660
That means you, Spe.
Until the next Tennoushou…

00:05:22.660 --> 00:05:24.010
Oh, yeah.

00:05:24.390 --> 00:05:26.960
How about you head home for a bit?

00:05:26.960 --> 00:05:27.510
Huh?

00:05:27.510 --> 00:05:30.330
You never went home for New Year's, did you?

00:05:30.330 --> 00:05:32.470
I-I'm heading home?

00:05:42.520 --> 00:05:44.260
<i>I'm back…</i>

00:05:59.720 --> 00:06:01.000
Welcome back.

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:03.090
Mom, I'm home!

00:06:03.090 --> 00:06:04.460
Get in.

00:06:06.230 --> 00:06:08.630
I haven't been able to race with you lately.

00:06:08.630 --> 00:06:09.690
I'm gonna run!

00:06:11.290 --> 00:06:11.720
Nope.

00:06:15.990 --> 00:06:17.350
Why?!

00:06:17.350 --> 00:06:19.100
Hey, why?

00:06:19.100 --> 00:06:22.440
You're supposed to be resting.

00:06:22.440 --> 00:06:25.070
Are you and my trainer ganging up on me?

00:06:25.070 --> 00:06:27.670
You can't run while you're here.

00:06:27.670 --> 00:06:28.870
What?!

00:06:28.870 --> 00:06:31.280
What's wrong with running for a little bit?

00:06:31.280 --> 00:06:34.740
Hey! What's wrong with that?!

00:06:35.370 --> 00:06:39.660
So, I'll be taking a break as well.

00:06:39.660 --> 00:06:40.620
That's a coincidence.

00:06:40.620 --> 00:06:44.360
{\an8}Mejiro
Ryan​

00:06:40.620 --> 00:06:44.360
{\an9}Mejiro
Dober

00:06:40.960 --> 00:06:43.710
All the three of us are
on break at the same time.

00:06:43.710 --> 00:06:46.300
It's nice to have all the
Mejiros in one place.

00:06:46.300 --> 00:06:48.600
Ryan, you're too laid back about this.

00:06:48.600 --> 00:06:52.680
It's not that easy to
stay in proper condition.

00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:54.640
I can't embarrass the Mejiro family name

00:06:54.640 --> 00:06:56.770
when I race with Team
Spica once the break is over.

00:06:57.730 --> 00:06:59.880
Hmm? What's wrong?

00:06:59.880 --> 00:07:01.990
McQueen, you've changed.

00:07:01.990 --> 00:07:05.610
Until not too long ago, you wouldn't have
minded us all getting a little rowdy.

00:07:06.920 --> 00:07:12.130
Someone taught me that sometimes changing
can bring about positive results.

00:07:12.130 --> 00:07:13.620
Wow.

00:07:13.620 --> 00:07:18.540
Now you only need to change how you
get way too intense about sweets.

00:07:19.930 --> 00:07:20.620
My.

00:07:21.130 --> 00:07:23.330
Forget about that!

00:07:23.330 --> 00:07:26.410
I'm going to be extremely upset if you
tell grandmother about that!

00:07:27.710 --> 00:07:29.020
You gotta take it!

00:07:27.710 --> 00:07:30.090
{\an8}Karaoke

00:07:29.020 --> 00:07:31.660
Somewhere else? Nope,
it's happening right here!

00:07:30.090 --> 00:07:33.090
{\an8}You gotta take it! Somewhere else?
Nope, it's happening right here!

00:07:31.660 --> 00:07:33.090
Step it!

00:07:37.180 --> 00:07:38.720
Prez!

00:07:39.090 --> 00:07:40.770
You really came?

00:07:40.770 --> 00:07:44.440
I really came? You seem just fine.

00:07:44.440 --> 00:07:47.170
You made it sound like you were depressed.

00:07:45.310 --> 00:07:48.190
{\an7}Tokai Teio
Hey, Prez…
I don't know what to do…
Maybe if I talked to you in person…
Actually, never mind
What's the matter?
Ughh…
I think I'm done…
Can you come to karaoke?
Do you want me to meet you there?
Yeah!
Yeah…

00:07:48.190 --> 00:07:52.150
You wouldn't have come unless I did that.

00:07:53.220 --> 00:07:55.000
Sorry for lying to you!

00:07:55.000 --> 00:07:57.380
But I really wanted to show you something.

00:07:57.380 --> 00:07:58.040
Take a look!

00:07:58.040 --> 00:07:59.170
Hmm?

00:08:00.100 --> 00:08:01.610
My song?

00:08:02.790 --> 00:08:04.800
I really practiced.

00:08:04.800 --> 00:08:08.800
I want to look good for my team out there.

00:08:09.890 --> 00:08:12.070
Well, I guess you're growing.

00:08:12.070 --> 00:08:13.830
Did you say something?

00:08:13.830 --> 00:08:14.890
It's nothing.

00:08:15.940 --> 00:08:17.640
You get one song, 'kay?

00:08:23.930 --> 00:08:26.500
I wanted something for winter.

00:08:26.500 --> 00:08:28.790
Why are we looking at race shoes?

00:08:28.790 --> 00:08:30.180
Why shouldn't we?

00:08:30.180 --> 00:08:32.570
I want something nice.

00:08:32.570 --> 00:08:35.010
Then just go home.

00:08:34.330 --> 00:08:36.250
{\an8}What was that? Then why don't—

00:08:40.810 --> 00:08:44.480
{\an7}Biwa Hayahide

00:08:40.810 --> 00:08:44.480
{\an9}Narita Brian

00:08:40.980 --> 00:08:44.220
It's been a while since we've
gone shopping together.

00:08:44.220 --> 00:08:46.000
I guess it's nice for a change.

00:08:46.420 --> 00:08:47.970
Wait up…

00:08:48.760 --> 00:08:51.100
It's Biwa Hayahide-senpai!

00:08:51.100 --> 00:08:53.050
Narita Brian-senpai is with her, too.

00:08:53.050 --> 00:08:55.260
You can tell they're strong
just by looking at them.

00:08:55.640 --> 00:08:58.040
Why did you want to come here today?

00:08:58.040 --> 00:09:01.560
I wanted to think about running
with my elder sister someday.

00:09:02.010 --> 00:09:04.730
You can call yourself strong
when you beat someone

00:09:04.730 --> 00:09:07.060
who you fully understand and
who fully understands you.

00:09:07.800 --> 00:09:09.200
I agree.

00:09:09.200 --> 00:09:12.940
It makes sense to start preparing
now for any future bouts.

00:09:14.090 --> 00:09:17.030
You always like to make
yourself sound smart, huh?

00:09:17.030 --> 00:09:19.700
What are you talking about?!

00:09:19.700 --> 00:09:22.950
Someone you understand
that also understands you…

00:09:22.950 --> 00:09:25.490
And if you beat them, you're truly strong.

00:09:29.810 --> 00:09:30.690
Hmph!

00:09:30.690 --> 00:09:32.490
I'm getting these shoes!

00:09:32.490 --> 00:09:34.550
Then I'm getting these!

00:09:41.930 --> 00:09:44.270
<i>I need to get back into
the groove with racing.</i>

00:09:51.110 --> 00:09:52.980
Why are you out of breath?

00:09:53.540 --> 00:09:56.070
You get caught peeking in the changing
room and had to run away?

00:09:56.500 --> 00:09:58.820
The Open Special one and
a half months from now

00:10:00.950 --> 00:10:04.040
is going to be your comeback race, Suzuka!

00:10:04.040 --> 00:10:04.670
What?

00:10:04.670 --> 00:10:05.540
Really?!

00:10:05.540 --> 00:10:07.940
I'm going to race?

00:10:08.920 --> 00:10:10.550
That's great, Suzuka!

00:10:10.550 --> 00:10:13.360
You should be happier!

00:10:13.360 --> 00:10:15.130
Finally, huh?

00:10:16.840 --> 00:10:18.940
It hasn't been officially announced yet,

00:10:18.940 --> 00:10:20.210
so don't tell anyone.

00:10:20.210 --> 00:10:22.310
Okay! No problem!

00:10:23.100 --> 00:10:25.810
No problem at all!

00:10:26.390 --> 00:10:28.170
Everyone's going to find out now.

00:10:29.520 --> 00:10:30.980
All right, Suzuka.

00:10:30.980 --> 00:10:33.870
Let's do what you need to do for this race!

00:10:33.870 --> 00:10:34.780
Right.

00:10:34.780 --> 00:10:37.900
In a race, you'll need a
strategy to handle the turns.

00:10:38.220 --> 00:10:41.650
Let's train with a real race in mind,
so we can handle that.

00:10:52.630 --> 00:10:54.100
It's almost time for dinner.

00:10:54.100 --> 00:10:55.900
Don't keep pouting forever.

00:10:55.900 --> 00:10:59.030
I made your favorite, carrot Salisbury steak.

00:10:59.030 --> 00:11:01.690
What's wrong with running for a little bit?!

00:11:05.640 --> 00:11:07.480
Spe, it's ready.

00:11:09.010 --> 00:11:11.270
Spe?

00:11:15.300 --> 00:11:16.360
These are…

00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:18.990
Whenever a letter comes from you,

00:11:19.640 --> 00:11:22.560
I read it with your other mother.

00:11:22.560 --> 00:11:24.540
It makes us twice as happy.

00:11:24.540 --> 00:11:25.540
What's this?

00:11:26.540 --> 00:11:28.790
{\an4}Satsukishou Competitors Announced!

00:11:31.290 --> 00:11:35.040
{\an4}Japanese Derby

00:11:31.290 --> 00:11:35.040
{\an8}But She Freezes Pathetically…

00:11:32.010 --> 00:11:33.830
She kept all of it.

00:11:35.040 --> 00:11:37.920
Spe, do you remember this?

00:11:37.920 --> 00:11:39.920
{\an8}Become the Best in Japan,
Special Week

00:11:43.880 --> 00:11:46.560
You were like a little kid back then,

00:11:46.980 --> 00:11:49.300
but you've worked really hard.

00:11:49.300 --> 00:11:53.090
I don't know if I can
become the best in Japan,

00:11:53.560 --> 00:11:57.360
but my trainer is going to let me
race in the Tennoushou and Japan Cup.

00:11:57.360 --> 00:11:59.690
You don't have to push yourself.

00:11:59.690 --> 00:12:01.070
Anyway, let's eat.

00:12:01.770 --> 00:12:02.660
Okay.

00:12:04.990 --> 00:12:08.990
{\an6}Umamusume

00:12:04.990 --> 00:12:08.990
{\an6}Pretty Derby

00:12:10.040 --> 00:12:11.460
Really?!

00:12:11.460 --> 00:12:13.530
It's all decided, then?

00:12:13.530 --> 00:12:15.170
<i>It's the Open Special, but yeah.</i>

00:12:15.170 --> 00:12:17.290
<i>When is it?!</i>

00:12:15.170 --> 00:12:22.420
{\an8}Silence Suzuka
Comeback Race Announced!!

00:12:17.290 --> 00:12:20.180
The day before your Japan Cup race.

00:12:20.180 --> 00:12:22.420
<i>I'll be cheering you on!</i>

00:12:22.420 --> 00:12:25.310
Everyone in Spica is doing great,

00:12:25.310 --> 00:12:26.760
I have to do well, too.

00:12:27.410 --> 00:12:31.600
All my fans, watch me in my Winning Concert!

00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:35.690
Time to show you what I'm made of!

00:12:36.520 --> 00:12:40.190
I'm not letting Vodka
hog the spotlight!

00:12:40.530 --> 00:12:42.440
I won't allow any shame
to come to the Mejiro family,

00:12:43.300 --> 00:12:45.950
and I'll bring honor to Spica!

00:12:45.950 --> 00:12:46.970
All right…

00:12:46.970 --> 00:12:48.370
Team Spica!

00:12:48.370 --> 00:12:50.890
We're doing great!

00:12:50.870 --> 00:12:55.580
{\an8}Suzuka-san

00:12:51.330 --> 00:12:54.570
<i>Spe-chan, let's talk lots when you get back.</i>

00:12:54.570 --> 00:12:55.580
Okay!

00:13:05.460 --> 00:13:07.800
I'm happy for you, Suzuka-san.

00:13:08.600 --> 00:13:10.630
Let me sit next to you.

00:13:13.300 --> 00:13:16.830
The stars out here are beautiful,

00:13:16.830 --> 00:13:21.490
but the glow sticks everyone holds up after
you take first are beautiful, too.

00:13:21.940 --> 00:13:23.860
Then I hope you'll be able
to come in first again.

00:13:27.490 --> 00:13:28.490
What's this?

00:13:28.490 --> 00:13:29.650
Open it.

00:13:31.490 --> 00:13:33.500
{\an8}Be the Best in Japan

00:13:32.050 --> 00:13:33.500
A horseshoe?

00:13:33.500 --> 00:13:35.770
I made that myself.

00:13:35.770 --> 00:13:36.650
What?

00:13:36.650 --> 00:13:37.940
Take a close look.

00:13:39.500 --> 00:13:42.500
{\an8}Be the Best in Japan

00:13:40.150 --> 00:13:42.500
Be the best in Japan…

00:13:42.500 --> 00:13:44.230
Will you use it?

00:13:44.230 --> 00:13:44.920
Yeah!

00:13:44.920 --> 00:13:47.260
I'll use it in the upcoming Tennoushou!

00:13:47.860 --> 00:13:49.300
Mom…

00:13:49.300 --> 00:13:50.520
What is it?

00:13:50.520 --> 00:13:52.730
I'm happy.

00:13:52.730 --> 00:13:53.520
Hmm?

00:13:53.520 --> 00:13:57.270
I'm happy that I have two moms.

00:13:57.650 --> 00:14:00.450
I'm happy that I get to
be your mom, too, Spe.

00:14:01.590 --> 00:14:04.990
I'm going to be the best in
Japan with this horseshoe!

00:14:09.460 --> 00:14:11.740
Then go run your heart out.

00:14:12.650 --> 00:14:13.430
Yeah!

00:14:33.640 --> 00:14:36.980
{\an4}Potato Snacks

00:14:33.640 --> 00:14:36.980
{\an8}Ikura

00:14:34.630 --> 00:14:36.980
How was Hokkaido?

00:14:36.980 --> 00:14:38.980
I'm all rested up!

00:14:38.980 --> 00:14:40.100
Trainer-san!

00:14:40.100 --> 00:14:42.760
Let's go train right now!

00:14:46.690 --> 00:14:50.470
Guess she's back to the way she
originally was after going home.

00:14:50.470 --> 00:14:52.020
That's Spe-chan for you.

00:14:52.020 --> 00:14:53.770
There's not much time until the Tennoushou.

00:14:53.770 --> 00:14:55.080
We're going to get you ready!

00:14:55.630 --> 00:14:56.550
Right!

00:15:43.460 --> 00:15:45.420
It's all ready, Suzuka-san!

00:15:46.600 --> 00:15:48.800
"Be the best in Japan."

00:15:48.800 --> 00:15:52.340
That's what you said you wanted to do
when you joined the team, right, Spe-chan?

00:15:52.340 --> 00:15:53.290
Yeah,

00:15:53.290 --> 00:15:57.100
but back then, I just wanted
to make my mom happy.

00:15:57.100 --> 00:15:58.840
That's not the case now?

00:15:58.840 --> 00:16:01.520
I still want to make my mom happy.

00:16:02.150 --> 00:16:06.940
But not just her. I want our trainer
and everyone on our team to be happy.

00:16:06.940 --> 00:16:08.810
But most of all…

00:16:10.260 --> 00:16:12.950
I want you to be happy, Suzuka-san.

00:16:14.200 --> 00:16:17.460
I'm going to win the Tennoushou
and the Japan Cup.

00:16:17.460 --> 00:16:20.450
I'll have people call me the
best horse girl in Japan.

00:16:20.450 --> 00:16:23.490
And then I'm going to race with you.

00:16:24.170 --> 00:16:25.850
Then I'm going to beat you.

00:16:27.330 --> 00:16:31.090
I don't just want to keep chasing after you.

00:16:31.090 --> 00:16:32.770
I want to be next to you.

00:16:33.750 --> 00:16:34.840
Me, too.

00:16:34.840 --> 00:16:35.470
Huh?

00:16:35.470 --> 00:16:37.330
I'm going to win my comeback race,

00:16:37.330 --> 00:16:39.350
win some big races,

00:16:39.910 --> 00:16:41.470
and then I'm going to America.

00:16:42.520 --> 00:16:43.850
I'm not going to give up.

00:16:44.390 --> 00:16:46.180
That was my dream.

00:16:48.970 --> 00:16:52.370
I'm going to become a horse girl that gives
everyone in the world something to dream of.

00:16:52.940 --> 00:16:53.960
Yeah.

00:16:54.580 --> 00:16:57.660
When my dream comes true, Spe-chan…

00:16:58.790 --> 00:17:00.090
Let's settle this…

00:17:01.930 --> 00:17:03.540
…as rivals.

00:17:05.640 --> 00:17:07.530
Right! It's a promise!

00:17:08.420 --> 00:17:12.800
{\an8}Tennoushou Fall

00:17:29.690 --> 00:17:31.560
<i>It's been one year since the tragedy.</i>

00:17:31.560 --> 00:17:34.570
<i>The time this year for the
fall Tennoushou has come.</i>

00:17:34.570 --> 00:17:37.810
Special Week will be running for Team Spica.

00:17:37.810 --> 00:17:39.160
After coming in 7th,

00:17:39.160 --> 00:17:42.260
<i>she's not as much of a
favorite this time around.</i>

00:17:42.260 --> 00:17:46.920
<i>Seiun Sky won the Sapporo Kinen,
so most eyes will be on her.</i>

00:17:46.920 --> 00:17:49.240
I don't like tight spaces.

00:17:48.980 --> 00:17:51.340
{\an7}King Halo

00:17:49.240 --> 00:17:51.380
Hurry up and get in.

00:17:53.620 --> 00:17:56.000
<i>Her weight is the same as in the Derby.</i>

00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:57.340
<i>We tightened things up well.</i>

00:17:57.340 --> 00:17:58.380
<i>I'm counting on you.</i>

00:17:58.380 --> 00:18:00.930
Trainer-san, where's Suzuka-san?

00:18:00.930 --> 00:18:02.670
Suzuka's not coming.

00:18:02.670 --> 00:18:05.090
What? Even though Spe-chan is racing?!

00:18:05.640 --> 00:18:09.810
She said she's Spe's rival, so she
has other things she needs to do.

00:18:15.560 --> 00:18:18.490
<i>Seiun Sky has finally entered the gates.</i>

00:18:30.520 --> 00:18:32.230
<i>For the honor of the plaque…</i>

00:18:32.230 --> 00:18:34.500
<i>Let the fall Tennoushou…</i>

00:18:35.940 --> 00:18:37.720
<i>…begin!</i>

00:18:39.340 --> 00:18:41.970
Go, Spe!

00:18:48.950 --> 00:18:50.810
<i>I need to get to the front quickly.</i>

00:18:50.810 --> 00:18:51.650
<i>King Halo,</i>

00:18:51.650 --> 00:18:54.480
and Seiun Sky behind her,
are in the middle of the pack.

00:18:59.370 --> 00:19:01.720
<i>I wonder how Spe-chan will make her move.</i>

00:19:03.450 --> 00:19:06.040
<i>Special Week is in the rear.</i>

00:19:06.040 --> 00:19:08.050
<i>When will she make her move?</i>

00:19:14.010 --> 00:19:15.420
<i>They've made the fourth turn!</i>

00:19:15.810 --> 00:19:17.460
<i>She's still in the rear!</i>

00:19:17.460 --> 00:19:19.380
<i>Is Special Week okay?</i>

00:19:19.380 --> 00:19:21.430
{\an8}They've entered the last stretch!

00:19:19.890 --> 00:19:22.390
<i>I can do this!</i>

00:19:22.390 --> 00:19:24.270
<i>They're all making their move!</i>

00:19:24.270 --> 00:19:24.850
<i>I can do this!</i>

00:19:27.320 --> 00:19:29.680
<i>Everyone's up front, so it's hard to run.</i>

00:19:30.100 --> 00:19:31.480
<i>But…</i>

00:19:32.230 --> 00:19:33.970
Then go run your heart out.

00:19:35.240 --> 00:19:36.940
<i>I'm going to run my heart out!</i>

00:19:39.860 --> 00:19:40.910
Senpai!

00:19:40.910 --> 00:19:41.530
She's fast!

00:19:41.530 --> 00:19:42.390
It's the hill!

00:19:42.390 --> 00:19:44.030
Get up there!

00:19:47.130 --> 00:19:50.000
<i>I'm still going to win…</i>

00:19:50.000 --> 00:19:52.580
Seiun Sky is fighting to keep up!

00:19:52.580 --> 00:19:54.880
<i>Will she manage to get back
ahead of Special Week?</i>

00:19:55.190 --> 00:19:57.380
<i>We're under 200 meters now!</i>

00:19:57.380 --> 00:20:00.630
<i>She's fast, but I'm not done!</i>

00:20:00.630 --> 00:20:02.720
<i>Special Week is making her way up!</i>

00:20:08.050 --> 00:20:09.600
<i>I don't want to lose.</i>

00:20:16.290 --> 00:20:17.690
<i>No matter how many times I lose…</i>

00:20:18.200 --> 00:20:19.320
<i>No matter how frustrated I get…</i>

00:20:23.810 --> 00:20:25.250
<i>I want to win!</i>

00:20:37.340 --> 00:20:40.590
Go, Special Week!

00:20:45.370 --> 00:20:46.550
<i>I want to…</i>

00:20:48.050 --> 00:20:50.390
<i>…win!</i>

00:20:50.390 --> 00:20:52.060
<i>Special Week!</i>

00:20:52.060 --> 00:20:54.580
<i>Special Week is in the lead!</i>

00:21:01.280 --> 00:21:04.070
{\an8}Tennoushou Fall

00:21:06.520 --> 00:21:10.160
<i>Special Week easily comes in first!</i>

00:21:14.600 --> 00:21:16.040
We did it!

00:21:20.340 --> 00:21:23.620
<i>Special Week has set a new record!</i>

00:21:23.620 --> 00:21:25.800
<i>She's made a magnificent comeback!</i>

00:21:26.570 --> 00:21:30.010
<i>We're expecting a lot from
her at the next Japan Cup!</i>

00:21:30.010 --> 00:21:32.020
Wow, a record!

00:21:32.020 --> 00:21:33.530
Good job!

00:21:34.420 --> 00:21:37.100
We have to work hard, too.

00:21:41.810 --> 00:21:43.970
You did well, Spe.

00:21:44.570 --> 00:21:47.700
Spe-chan's gotten faster.

00:21:47.700 --> 00:21:48.650
Yeah.

00:21:48.650 --> 00:21:51.160
You seem kind of happy.

00:21:51.930 --> 00:21:55.830
The stronger my rivals,
the stronger I become.

00:21:59.590 --> 00:22:01.060
That's right.

00:22:25.740 --> 00:22:28.810
In a dash, in a flash,
just a little more now,

00:22:28.810 --> 00:22:31.520
each new race like a dream neverending

00:22:31.520 --> 00:22:34.330
Every one of us will blaze a
trail aimed right for the stars

00:22:34.330 --> 00:22:39.500
Together we'll run! Let's
go! Our starting gate!

00:22:48.630 --> 00:22:53.960
With curiosity in hand, go tug
on tomorrow's tail and say hello

00:22:53.960 --> 00:22:58.960
It's right there, so go on and close
the gap now (Right here and now!)

00:22:59.670 --> 00:23:05.050
Can't play by the rules they tell
you! Gotta learn it all by experience!

00:23:05.050 --> 00:23:09.990
If we just plan to run for the
end, everything will turn out okay!

00:23:10.150 --> 00:23:14.020
Can't get me down,
hesitate, or go too slowly!

00:23:15.770 --> 00:23:19.740
We know that deep in our hearts is a song

00:23:19.820 --> 00:23:22.960
that sings "give it your all"! Make it shine!

00:23:23.540 --> 00:23:26.760
In a dash, in a flash, just a
little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:26.760 --> 00:23:29.510
every step like the wind
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:29.510 --> 00:23:32.410
A twinkling star that we wear
on our sleeves (But only one!)

00:23:32.410 --> 00:23:34.710
Let's let our hearts race
together as one! (Grow up! Shine!)

00:23:34.710 --> 00:23:37.840
One more step, one more push,
just a little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:37.840 --> 00:23:40.490
each new race like a dream
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:40.490 --> 00:23:43.340
Every one of us will see
our path to the very end!

00:23:43.340 --> 00:23:49.070
Let's run now, everyone!
Let's go! Our starting gate!

